On Spring Break this week but really wanted to share this. April and May are fantastic times to add a new dog to the family. Please consider rescue. Some animals that end up in shelters carry no wounds, some look like this just on the outside, some just on the inside, and some are both emotionally and physically wounded - all by no fault of their own. The goal of an adopter is to realize this, determine what healing needs to happen and slowly and compassionately address each cut and tear. There is no better feeling than watching a helpless animal in your care build themselves back up. As a parent this is a priceless lesson you can teach your children. As the leader in your family, you can pay tutors, put your kids on teams, tell them stories of the bravery and courage of others, but the lessons learned through rescue cannot be bought or told. The lessons learned through rescue build better humans and in turn the society so many are clamoring for. Just food for thought. #adoptdontshop

Current and former UND players not only objected to the cessation of the program, but to the way it was handled, accusing the university of informing the media while the team was still practicing. ¿Qué es Flow Jac System? Flow Jac System es el último sistema de ortodoncia clínicamente comprobado en donde los arcos de alambre persisten y el bracket es reemplazado por un mini-tubo.  Desarrollado para proporcionar al paciente altos estándares de confort mientras corrige la posición de los dientes durante el tratamiento. Basado en principios biológicos del movimiento dental, Flow Jac System, utiliza alambres de aleaciones de alta tecnología con propiedades biomecánicas altamente compatibles con el tejido humano y materiales dentales adhesivos de última generación. La combinación sinérgica de los elementos de este sistema, en donde los arcos de alambre persisten y el bracket desaparece, brinda al paciente altos niveles de estética con procedimientos de ortodoncia mucho más confortables disminuyendo en un alto porcentaje los requerimientos de higiene oral, comparados con los de un tratamiento convencional.  Visítanos en nuestras sedes. Somos expertos en utilizar este procedimiento !!! Even for the most conservative guests, I push for a skin taper in the nape for a number of reasons. A skin taper removes the unwanted length at the lower neck while eliminating the need for a lineup on the bottom hairline. I've always felt that a stamped-in hairline tends to look too artificial and appears like a line of demarcation in the next couple of weeks as the hair grows out. A skin taper solves this issue by not leaving a line to begin with, allowing the hairs at the nape to grow out as evenly as possible. Some guests may resist this idea, as they may be comfortable with the type of cut they have been getting. But it's important to introduce new concepts and aesthetics to clients as it gives them the option of staying modern and relevant. ___ Tag someone who you would like to introduce this to!  Δ

#chicago #illinois #usa🇺🇸 A long time ago, when the earth was still green, There were more kinds of animals than you've ever seen; They'd run around free while the earth was being born, The loveliest of all was the Unicorn.  There was green alligators and long-necked geese, Some humpty-backed camels and some chimpanzees, Some cats and rats and elephants, but sure as you're born, The loveliest of all was the Unicorn.  Now God seen some sinnin' and it gave Him pain. And He said, "Stand back, I'm going to make it rain." He said, "Hey, brother Noah, I'll tell you what to do. Build me a floating zoo." And take some of them green alligators and long-necked geese, Some humpty-backed camels and some chimpanzees, Some cats and rats and elephants, but sure as you're born, Don't you forget my Unicorn." Old Noah was there to answer the call, He finished up making the Ark just as the rain started fallin', He marched in the animals two by two And he called out as they went through, "Hey, Lord: I've got yer.... Green alligators and long-necked geese, Some humpty-backed camels and some chimpanzees, Some cats and rats and elephants, but Lord, I'm so forlorn, I just can't see no Unicorn." Old Noah looked out into the driving rain, Them Unicorns was hiding, playing silly games, Kicking and splashing while the rain was pouring, Oh, them silly Unicorns.  There was green alligators and long-necked geese, Some humpty-backed camels and some chimpanzees, Noah cried, "Close the doors 'cause the rain is pourin', And we just can't wait for no Unicorns." The Ark started movin', it drifted with the tide, Them Unicorns looked up from the rock and they cried, And the waters came down and sorta floated them away, That's why you'll never see a Unicorn, to this very day.  You'll see green alligators and long-necked geese, Some humpty-backed camels and some chimpanzees, Some cats and rats and elephants, but sure as you're born, You're never gonna see no Unicorn. ~ Irish Rovers #abc7chicago #cherylscottwx

Bilo je trenutaka kad smo svi želeli da se sve ovo završi i trenutaka kada se niko nije slagao, kad su svi bili napeti, smoreni, i na korak od odustajanja, ali uspeli smo da izguramo ovo do kraja i drago mi je da je to bilo sa ovom grupom ljudi.  Volim vas najviše i hvala vam na prelepih 6 meseci. Nadam se da ćemo svi raditi zajendo sledeću predstavu i da će biti još više smejanja (0% tenzije), i još više zabave! Oie pessoal, a Universidade de Chicago está oferecendo duas bolsas de verão, com o objetivo de possibilitar que jovens talentosos do Brasil, México​ e Vietnã tenham a experiência de estudar e morar em uma universidade norte-americana de ponta, então se você é um estudante do ensino médio e está à procura de oportunidades para fazer um intercâmbio, não perca essa oportunidade. Os alunos selecionados para o programa receberão uma bolsa completa que inclui gastos com o visto; passagens áreas de ida e volta para os EUA; matrícula no curso; acomodação e alimentação; custos de vida e residência no campus e seguro saúde. James Billington (1847 - December 13, 1901) was an executioner of England from 1884 to 1901. He was born in Preston, Lancashire. Billington had a "lifelong fascination" with hanging, and made replica gallows in his back yard on which he practiced with weights and dummies and, it was rumored locally, stray dogs and cats. After the death of William Marwood in 1883, the position opened up for a new Executioner of the City of London. Billington was 1 of the 3 on the shortlist to be the next executioner but the job was given to Bartholomew Binns. Billington wrote letters to English authorities offering to be a hangman and he was accepted by the authorities in Yorkshire. Billington's first execution was Joseph Laycock at Armley Gaol in Leeds, on August 26, 1884. Laylock was convicted of murdering his wife and 4 children. In 1891, Billington became the Chief Executioner over Great Britain and Ireland. Billington executed serial poisoner Thomas Neill Cream on November 15, 1892. Billington claimed Cream's last words were "I am Jack" implying he was Jack the Ripper but Cream was in Chicago at the time of the Ripper murders. Billington's final execution was Patrick McKenna on November 13, 1901 after McKenna was sentenced to hanging for the murder of his wife with a razor while in a rage for not giving him money to buy beer. #1800s #19century #history #execution #death #hang #hangman #jobs #England #Ireland #GreatBritain #Preston #Lancashire #Yorkshire #gallows #trapdoor #London #city #murder #razors #money #beer #cream #jack #Chicago #police #jail #wife #children #trial

#QuannaBrown, from #Chicago, decided to have the operation after her pregnancy weight knocked her body confidence. But just four days after the surgery, the mum-of-two woke up in excruciating pain like her ‘skin was ripping apart’. She said: ‘I’d never had surgery before so at first I thought it was normal. ‘I could smell it and I could see all this puss and blood like it was infected.’ Quanna had to stay in hospital for 50 days and undergo five more surgeries. Now pregnant with her third child, the 34-year-old has been left with a deformed stomach and struggles to look at herself in the mirror. Quanna insisted she did a lot of research before deciding on a doctor, who she has decided not to name. ‘I was very happy on the day of the surgery. I woke up bright and early and I was very excited, I went shopping, I wanted something new to wear after,’ she said. But the next day, Quanna said she was in so much pain it felt like her bandages were wrapped too tightly. ‘The doctor said he’d never seen anything like this before and gave me antibiotics,’ she said. ‘But my parents demanded that they fix me. My insides were opened and I was ripped. ‘He redid the wounds and sent me home. The next time I went back in wasn’t there and his partner looked at me but also sent me home afterwards.’ Unable to move, Quanna was rushed to the emergency room the next day. ‘They saved my life,’ she said. ‘I barley remember it. I just remember one of the doctor’s face, she was looking so angry at what happened to me.’ She stayed in hospital for over 50 days and had five surgeries to remove skin and tissue as well as skin grafts. She said: ‘When I got released from Hospital, I wasn’t able to walk straight and I was on a cane, I was back and forth in hospital with blood clots, I spent two more weeks in hospital and I still wasn’t feeling well, and I had to do something. ‘My turning point came when my daughter asked for a bowl of cereal and I couldn’t get it for her.’ Now on the recovery, Quanna said her children have been her lifeline. ‘I take care of my kids, they are my main concerns. I’m excited for my miracle baby and I am excited to just to be Alive, she said.

#Chicago and its architecture have centuries of stories to tell, and 213 W. Institute Pl. is no exception. While renovating the #RiverNorth brick building, we uncovered a bicycle factory sign from the 1800's buried by hundreds of years of facade.  Intrigued, we dug further and found the factory was ran by Gormully & Jeffrey MFG Co. and manufactured bicycles under the Rambler brand. At one time Gormully & Jeffrey were the 2nd largest bicycle manufacturers in the country! Interested in knowing more about 213's past? Take a walk through our North stairwell! Frankie Yale was a young kid when his life of crime would get started. A friend of Johnny Torri he would find himself in the Five Points Gang in New York. A dozen murders by 21 Yale was a tough no nonsense gangster. With the move of Torrio to Chicago Yale would find himself in charge of almost all the rackets in the gang which included Extortion,Brothels, protection. With money made from the rackets Yale would buy a bar know as the Harvard Inn in Coney Island and employed  by Yale was a young man named Al Capone. Its the Harvard Inn where Capone earned his name scarface in a fight. Durning the beginning of prohibition Torrio wanted to expanded Jim Colosimos business to include illegal alcohol not wanting to expand Torrio would bring to Chicago Yale to eliminate Colosimo. With prohibition in full effect most illegal alcohol was coming from the Unione Siciliane where it was rumored that Yale was the president. After the retirement of Torrio a new Boss of The Outfit would emerge his name Capone. Capone would get alcohol from Yale which was ship from Brooklyn to Chicago. After many of Capone shipments were hijacked  never making it to Chicago Capone felt something was up and he was right. Sending a friend to spy on Yale James DeAmato was able to confimn the suspicious of Capone. Yale was hijacking his own shipments and reselling them to Capone. With this act of betrayal and Yale trying to take over parts of Capone area a contact was put out. On July 1st, 1928 Yales was driving and forced into a curb by another car. A barrage of bullets flew from the car and riddle Yales body. Its said that one of the guns recovered was a Tommy Gun the first time it had been used in a New York killing. Envie de testé un peu de montagne pour me mettre à l'épreuve 😃. 20km en montagne je peux vous dire sa n'a rien à voir avec 20km de plat/sémi plat 😂😂😂 En tout cas j'ai pu apprendre 2-3 choses de super, déjà je surkiffe la grimpe 😍😍😍😍 (âme de grimpeur ?) ensuite que malgré le fait que c'était la première fois que j attaquait de la montagne j'ai plutôt un bon niveaux 😤 ( j'ai pu laissé 3 cyclistes sur le carreaux 😂 ) !  Petit point négatif pour la déscente car les voitures sont peu enclin à laissé de la place et pas trop rassuré (50-55km/h dans la descente) avec les trou et les voitures c'était plus stressant qu'autre chose.  Super journée au top avec le soleil, de nouvels limite dépassé et la prochaine fois je monte jusqu'au col 😎 ! (Pour info la je suis monté à 1 082m)

A huge congrats to #bozicvoicestudio student Wasif Sami, who made his 'Broadway Debut' with the  Pixie Dust Players in a production of the Broadway Musical CHICAGO at The Ambassador Theater, March 21, 2017. The surprise production was to honor the 90th birthday of the musical composer John Kander and to announce the creation of CHICAGO (High School Edition). Wasif (front/left) made his ‘Broadway debut’ in the company of the great legends, Chita Rivera, Joel Grey, James Naughton, Bebe Neuwirth and many others, who all made surprise appearances. The corner of Gunnison Street and Magnolia Avenue didn't always carry that name. It used to be Lafayette Street and Magnolia Avenue until the 1930's, when the city sought to rename duplicate streets and Lafayette Avenue on the southside won out. With heavy hearts our loved @dakruse has risen above and heaven certainly gained one angel rockstar.  Our hearts are broken and Chicago's heart is too...Donnie Kruse touched everyone he encountered, with greatest of his Irish love and sweetest rock n roll in his heart always, he made every time in life grand. Donnie lived strong fighting the good fight everyday, always with a twinkle in his eye and a smile that would put sunshine into your day. He built a neighborhood strong bringing together all walks of life from the homeless to the rockstars of the world treating everyone the same. He also looked out for all the little guys and underdogs out there too and was the  first one to bring Mustard Girl All American Mustards to @stanleyschicago and to the Chicago restaurant scene, which I was forever indebted. Donnie was always the biggest support to my heart as well as to all hearts of many ages he touched through and through. Donnie will forever be the smiling stars in our nights reminding us to keep looking up, keep the rock n roll in our hearts, to always love and to keep on truckin always too. Biggest love and prayers to his dearest family and friends out there, forever Donnie we miss and love you.. 💛🙏🏻🍀💛🙏🏻💛 " We are the music makers , and we are the dreamers of dreams, Wandering by lone sea-breakers, and sitting by desolate streams;- World losers and world forsakers, on whom the pale moon gleams: Yet we are the movers and shakers of the world forever, it seems." ~Arthur O'Shaunessey #stanleys #restaurant #king #mustardgirl #chicago #stanburger #karokeking #donniekruse

Salvatore Capone, better known as Frank was the elder brother of Chicago Outfit boss Alphonse Capone. Growing up in New York, both Frank and Al became involved in the infamous "Five Points Gang" with mobster John Torrio. By 1918, Torrio had moved to Chicago to help a relative defend his rackets, and Torrio soon asked Al and later Frank to join him there. Frank, a man who experts say could have written an even bloodier chapter in American crime than his infamous brother had a dedication to bloodletting and more savage instincts than Al. Al always exercised a certain patience. His credo, absorbed from the teachings of Johnny Torrio, was “always try to deal before you have to kill.” Frank's observation was, "You never get no back talk from no corpse.” He died at the age 29 after being shot by police during the Capones take over of Cicero in 1924. #SalvatoreCapone #FrankCapone #ChocagoOutfit #ChicagoMob #Chicago #Cicero

When I first started running it was because I thought it would be a quick way to drop weight. Never once did I ever imagine I would come to love it. There's something addicting about saying no to your mind and body when both are telling you to stop. Combine these feelings with an amazing group of individuals and you might never want to stop (s/o to the NRC Chicago pacers). It is for this reason as well as being inspired by all of these lovely individuals that I have finally decided to sign up for a race! On July 16th I will be running the @runrocknroll half in my favorite city ❤️. I could've chosen to pay the $90 entry fee but why do that when I can raise money for such an amazing cause? Everyday i remind myself just how blessed I am to be active and healthy. Many of us take it for granted. This is why i am choosing to run for more than myself. I'm running for all the kids out there who aren't as fortunate as I am right now by fundraising for @stjude. It would mean the world to me if you guys could help me reach my goal of $500! The link is in my bio fam 💕 Any amount would be a tremendous help. Hope you guys all have a wonderful week and remember that it's #mondaymotivation ....so y'all better be plannin on how you're crushing your goals this week 🙌🏽

I think the juxtaposition of skyscrapers to this ancient technology is a fascinating visual reminder of how far we human  beings have advanced, in a relatively short period of time. In honor of the #Cubs home opener tonight, here's a throwback from last year freezing my butt off in the bleachers with some of my favorite people.

#shutdownchicagoslaughterhouses  There is a great injustice happening at Park Packing Co and every other slaughterhouse in this city and beyond. We came to stop this truck because every animal trapped inside does not deserve to die. Every lamb and piglet we met is someone's daughter, son, sister, or brother. Every lamb and piglet is someone.  These animals are not disposable objects for human pleasure. They are not things, they are animals and they are people. Just like us.  As activists it is our duty to speak out against this horrible atrocity, to directly confront the violence. This atrocity happens in the dead of night because it's too shameful for the public to witness or know about.  We bared witness today to offer comfort and kindness to those who have never known either. Not from humans. They receive comfort from one another and only for a few brief minutes from us today in the moments before they were killed.  Right now, everyone who they've ever known will die with them inside that slaughterhouse. They must watch their loved ones be butchered before their very eyes. How is this okay? How is this humane?  There is no humane way to kill someone who does not want to die. There is no way to exploit someone and call it humane. It's not food, it's violence.  More photos and vids coming. Thanks all for being brave and bearing witness to this atrocity today.

Who's your MVP? The Beard or The Brodie? Now there's a huge MVP rivalry between the two. Both players are triple double machines and both are very dominant. Now I personally think Harden should win MVP just by a tiny bit and I'll explain why. Harden came from a sixth man to an All-Star and MVP candidate. Harden led his team from 8th seed in the west to the 3rd seed in the west. While on the other hand, Russ is just averaging triple doubles and scoring them every night. Now both of their teams' are in the playoff spots right now. And Harden did prove a point saying that he thought that being MVP is about winning. And I do agree on what he's saying. For example, let's take it back to 2011. Rose was a MVP candidate and lead his team to 62-20 record with his team being the best team in the league. Rose averaging great stats and having the best record is a little equivalent to Harden almost averaging a triple double (just by two rebounds off) and having the third best team in the league. So I personally believe Harden should win. Russell Westbrook is a great player and is the best PG out there. Russ does deserve to win MVP. But I believe that winning is a big essential into being placed in the MVP spot. So my vote goes to James Harden. Now a lot of you guys or most of you guys may disagree. But again both players have their pros and cons and possibly or most likely Russell Westbrook might win due to his dominance. So my vote goes to Harden. I have nothing against Russ, but I'm just stating my opinion. You guys may comment your opinion down below if you may like to. If you guys go look at the MVP ladder by week, you'll see that Harden and Westbrook just go back and forth at it. If the NBA couldn't decide, the co-MVP idea is still valid in my book.  #drose #derrickrose #derrick #rose #chicago #newyork #nyk #nyknicks #knicks #bulls #adidas #adidashoops #adidasbasketball #mvp #nba #carmelo #anthony #jimmy #butler #mj #joakim #noah #courtney #lee #brandon #jennings #25 #basketball #motivation

Here at #venusmedspa we have people ask us ALL the time.✨✨ “How much #filler do I need?” ✨✨ “How long will it last?”✨✨ Here is an #awesome visual of actually HOW MUCH filler is in a syringe.✨✨ Surprisingly it’s not that much...✨✨ For example it’s very easy to use one #syringe of filler in the lips and still look natural.✨✨ It’s takes FIVE syringes of filler to equal ONE teaspoon. Seems like a tiny amount right? ✨✨ This is true but also where water comes into play. The water within your #body is drawn to the filler and helps to make it look more volumous. So drink your #water for better results;) ✨✨But this is also where #education as practitioners is important.✨✨ Nearly every patient we see is a candidate for multiple syringes. And most patients will not get a full #correction with only one syringe.✨✨ At this point it’s good to build and see your injector every few months until correction is achieved....✨✨

Here are ten more (reeeeeeally) old photos in honor of #nationalsiblingsday because... well, 1970s childrens' fashions. 😂😂😂 My mom sent me eight of these this morning after I asked her for some photos of all five of us kids. The others, I already had. They're not in chronological order, but I can say that the first seven are from growing up in Chicago and the rest are from our days as Florida residents. Sometimes it feels foreign raising  an only child after growing up in a family of five kids. But, I also know that being the only child has its perks, too. And it's really all Isaac has ever known, so it must not feel foreign to him. He still asks if we could adopt him a brother or sister from time to time. Wish the answer could be what he wants to hear. I hope he'll grow up to have a bunch of kids. The bell tower of St. James Cathedral, located at 65 E Huron Street in the Gold Coast Neighborhood of Chicago, IL. The church was originally designed in 1855, but most of it was ruined during the Great Chicago Fire of 1871.  The bell tower, however, survived the Great Fire, and thus, is older than the rest of the current Cathedral.  It is charred at the top, partly because of the fire, but also perhaps because of the ravages of the industrial revolution.  It shows the Gothic revival architecture of the time, with the pointed arches of the windows, and it is made out of Athens Marble (like the Water Tower and Holy Name Cathedral). #digitalchicago #relg320 #LFC #sociology #anthropology #archaeology #architecture #gothic #chicago #religion #cathedral #episcopal #tower #industry #culture #material #marble #urban

At UJI, another secret spot for the best Cherry Blossom watching. There are about 2.000 Sakura trees at the Byodoin Garden and along the Uji Riverside.  Uji (宇治) is a small city situated between Kyoto and Nara, two of Japan's most famous historical and cultural centers. Its proximity to these two former capitals resulted in Uji's early development as a cultural center in its own right. At the height of political power of the Fujiwara clan in the Heian Period (794 to 1192), buildings such as Byodoin Temple and Ujigami Shrine, the oldest extant shrine in Japan, were contructed in Uji. Uji is also famous for its green tea.  There are 2 top attractions here are Byodoin Temple and Uji River.  Byodoin Temple is a striking example of Buddhist Pure Land (Jodo) architecture. Together with its garden, the temple represents the Pure Land Paradise and was influential on later temple construction. Byodoin was initially built in 998 as a countryside retreat villa for the powerful politician Fujiwara no Michinaga, not as a temple. Uji river is famous its birds fish catching attractions. Visitors can sail along the river enjoying the scenery of the riversides.  There a lot of small restaurants, tea house and greentea dessert cafe.  Most of the visitors here are local Japanese, not crowded at all and you can enjoy a relax moment here watching the beautiful cherry blossom.  Uji, Japan

Muitas cidades são marcadas pelos seus grandes símbolos, esculturas e monumentos. Impossível não associar o Cristo Redentor ao Rio de Janeiro, o letreiro de Hollywood a Los Angeles ou Coliseu a Roma.  #Chicago também tem o seu cartão-postal. E em se tratando de uma cidade caracterizada por sua beleza arquitetônica, nada melhor do que este símbolo ser uma linda escultura!  Localizada no meio do Millenium Park, o parque mais famoso de Chicago, a #CloudGate foi oficialmente inaugurada em 2006. Projetada pelo artista indo-britânico Anish Kapoor, a escultura logo tornou-se um dos pontos mais famosos da "cidade dos ventos". Apelidada de "The Bean", ou "O Feijão", por conta de seu formato, a Cloud Gate é feita de aço, e reflete de maneira brilhante e poética o belo skyline de Chicago.  Inspirada pelo mercúrio em estado líquido, a superfície da escultura reflete e distorce o panorama urbano da cidade. Os visitantes podem andar ao seu redor e mesmo debaixo, já que o arco tem 3,7 m de altura. Na zona inferior está o "omphalos" (grego para umbigo), uma câmara côncava que altera e multiplica reflexões. A escultura incorpora muitos dos temas artísticos de Kapoor, sendo popular entre os turistas pelas suas possibilidades fotográficas únicas.  #designurbano #arquiteturapelomundo 🇺🇲✨

#TheWord via @fortunemag  Shares in #United Continental Holdings Inc. were falling 2.8% in morning action on Tuesday, as the airline continued to draw flak for having a passenger forcibly dragged off a plane Sunday. If the carrier’s stock is that much lower at the closing bell, United UAL-2.75%  will have about $600 million wiped off its market capitalization. The company’s market cap was $22.5 billion as of Monday’s close, according to FactSet data ----------------------------- Tuesday’s slump suggests many investors think the carrier’s business could suffer given the furor over the incident. Videos of the bloodied passenger being dragged off the plane by law enforcement have been widely shared on social media ----------------------------- United said it had asked Sunday for four volunteers to leave the plane due to overbooking, and one customer refused to give up his seat on the full flight from Chicago’s #OHare International Airport to #Louisville, #Ky. #Chicago #unitedairlines

Pierre-August Renoir, French (1841-1919), 'Luncheon of the Boating Party' 1880-1881. This painting captures the atmosphere as Renoir's friends shared food & drinks on the balcony overlooking the Seine River at the Maison Fournaise Restaurant in Chatou. This was a popular gathering place for Parisians to rent rowing skiffs, eat & drink, and spend the evening. Renoir composed this scene over many months, painting the individual figures when the models (his friends) were available, & adding the stripped awning along the top edge. The painting has numerous popular culture references. Jean-Pierre Jeunet's film 'Amelie' is one prominent reference, with the woman right of center (Amelie?) sipping a glass, gazing uninterested as everyone around her is engaged & enjoying the day. The painting is also referenced in Susan Vreelands 2007 novel with the same name. At the 7th Impressionist Exhibit in 1882, it received wide praise as one of the best things Renoir had painted. And beneath, a playful spring luncheon collaboration. #thefestivefrog #aperfectevent

19-month-old Syrian refugee Sham Haj Khalad wears her grandfather's glasses at her home Friday, April 14, 2017, in Skokie, Ill. Fleeing the civil war in Syria, Sham's grandfather Khaled Haj Khalaf and his wife, Fattoum Bakir, came to Chicago in September 2016 with three of their children, but their oldest daughter Baraa Haj Khalaf and her family were denied entry in January of this year after President Donald Trump's immigration order banning all immigrants from Syria. Baraa, her husband Abdulmajeed and Sham spent two years in a Turkish refugee camp for the proper paperwork, interviews and background checks required to come to America. They were all finally reunited in February and now live together in the same apartment building.
